OL,3,CGovernment to crackdown on child
OL,4,Cbenefit claims from abroad
OL,6,FThe trial was carried out by the
OL,7,FPublic Sector Fraud Authority, the
OL,8,FHome Office and HMRC under the Digital
OL,9,FEconomy Act.
OL,11,FIt matched a random sample of 200,000
OL,12,Fchild benefit records with
OL,13,Finternational travel data to find
OL,14,Fthose who were wrongly claiming
OL,15,Fpayment.
OL,17,FThe government made clear that every
OL,18,Fcase is reviewed by a human
OL,19,Finvestigator and, as part of
OL,20,Finvestigations, HMRC would contact
OL,21,Ffamilies directly.
